# Tailwind CSS Best Practices

Comprehensive guide for building scalable, responsive designs with Tailwind CSS v4. Reference when styling components, creating layouts, or customizing the theme.

## Core Principles

### Mobile-First Responsive Design

Always start with base styles for mobile, then add responsive prefixes for larger screens. Never define only `md:` or `lg:` classes without base styles.

**Correct:**
```tsx
<div className="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:justify-center">
  <p>Works on all screen sizes</p>
</div>
```

**Incorrect:**
```tsx
<div className="md:flex md:justify-center">
  <p>Broken on mobile!</p>
</div>
```

### Utility-First Workflow

Apply utility classes directly in JSX for rapid development. Avoid creating custom CSS classes unless absolutely necessary.

**Prefer:**
```tsx
<button className="px-4 py-2 bg-blue-500 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-600">
  Click me
</button>
```

### Design Tokens with @theme

Use Tailwind v4's `@theme` directive to define custom design tokens in your CSS.

```css
@theme {
  --font-display: "Satoshi", "sans-serif";
  --breakpoint-3xl: 120rem;
  --color-avocado-100: oklch(0.9 0.1 120);
}
```

### Color System

Tailwind provides a default color palette. Use semantic names for consistency:

- Backgrounds: `bg-white`, `bg-gray-50`, `bg-gray-900`
- Text: `text-gray-500`, `text-gray-900`
- Borders: `border-gray-200`, `border-gray-700`
- Accents: `text-emerald-500`, `bg-blue-600`

### Spacing Scale

Use the default spacing scale consistently:
- `p-4`, `m-4` = 1rem (16px)
- `gap-4` = 1rem between flex/grid items
- `space-y-4` = margin between stacked elements

### Component Patterns

**Cards:**
```tsx
<div className="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm border border-gray-100 p-4">
  Content
</div>
```

**Buttons:**
```tsx
<button className="px-4 py-2 bg-emerald-600 text-white font-medium rounded-lg 
                   hover:bg-emerald-700 active:scale-[0.98] transition-all">
  Label
</button>
```

**Inputs:**
```tsx
<input className="w-full p-3 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg 
                  focus:ring-2 focus:ring-emerald-500 outline-none" />
```

### Dark Mode

Use `dark:` prefix for dark mode variants:
```tsx
<div className="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">
  Content
</div>
```

### Container Constraints

Constrain content width on desktop to prevent spanning full width:
```tsx
<div className="w-full max-w-md mx-auto">
  {/* Content centered with max width */}
</div>
```

### Breakpoints (Default)

- Default (base): mobile
- `sm`: 640px
- `md`: 768px
- `lg`: 1024px
- `xl`: 1280px
- `2xl`: 1536px

### Common Mistakes to Avoid

1. **Class soup** - Extract repeated class combinations into components
2. **Arbitrary values overuse** - Prefer default scale over `h-[123px]`
3. **Magic numbers** - Avoid `top-[3.14159rem]`, use config theme
4. **Missing focus states** - Always include `focus:ring` for interactive elements
5. **Not using `mx-auto`** - Containers need centering on desktop

## When to Apply

- Creating new components
- Styling forms, cards, buttons
- Building responsive layouts
- Implementing dark mode
- Customizing theme colors/spacing
